---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Privacy & boundaries — Meish"
  description="Trust is the product. No hidden use, no staff surveillance, no individual scoring, no promises made on a property's behalf."
>
  <section class="section container">
    <p class="eyebrow">Privacy &amp; boundaries</p>
    <h1>Trust is the product.</h1>
    <p class="lead">Meish only works if guests and staff trust it. So we hold hard lines — not
      because a regulation forces us to, but because breaking them would break the thing we sell.</p>

    <h2>What Meish does not do</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>No hidden use.</strong> People are never observed covertly for Meish work.</li>
      <li><strong>No staff surveillance.</strong> We never score, rank, or profile individual employees.</li>
      <li><strong>No individual guest scoring.</strong> We read patterns and signals, not people.</li>
      <li><strong>No public shaming.</strong> Findings go to the hotel, never to the internet.</li>
      <li><strong>No sensitive data</strong> without a clear reason and explicit consent.</li>
      <li><strong>No promises made on a property's behalf</strong> without the hotel's approval.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How guest signals are handled (Clara)</h2>
    <p>Guests share what helps their stay — parking, arrival, breakfast, accessibility, and how
      they'd like to feel. Clara turns that into a staff-facing digest. Information travels with
      the guest so nobody has to ask twice. Staff review and approve; Clara suggests, humans decide.</p>

    <h2>Your choices</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Consent is explicit and revocable.</li>
      <li>You can ask what we hold and have it removed.</li>
      <li>Contact: <a href="mailto:moona.m@meish.work">moona.m@meish.work</a></li>
    </ul>

    <p><small>Draft for legal review — data controller / legal entity line, retention periods,
      and sub-processors to be confirmed before final publish.</small></p>
  </section>
</Base>
